$:/plugins/tiddlywiki/tiddloid-tweaks/co.text:
These settings apply to the Tiddloid client. !!Appearance Apply theme color to system bars: <$select tiddler="$:/config/Tiddloid/ApplyTheme" default="Enabled"> Hide toolbar on loading complete: <$select tiddler="$:/config/Tiddloid/HideToolbar" default="Disabled"> !!Data If you want to backup your wiki list, click this link and check `INTERNAL/Android/data/top.donmor.tiddloid/files/` on your device.
Export data !!Custom actions Click the button below to open or create a config tiddler. The type of this tiddler should be `application/json` and it should be formatted like this: ``` [ { "name": "", "icon": "", "action": "" }, { "name": "act2", "action": "alert('message2')" } ] ``` <$button to="$:/config/Tiddloid/CustomActions.json">Configure custom actions
$:/plugins/tiddlywiki/tiddloid-tweaks/co.title: $:/plugins/tiddlywiki/tiddloid-tweaks/config
$:/plugins/tiddlywiki/tiddloid-tweaks/co.caption: Tiddloid Tweaks

$:/plugins/tiddlywiki/tiddloid-tweaks/re.text:
This plugin applies appearance tweaks to Tiddloid client. Currently it have these features:

* Hiding the toolbar when the file is fully loaded (Thanks to jdjdjdjdjdjd's [[idea|https://github.com/donmor/Tiddloid/issues/7]])
* Making the toolbar (as well as system status bar and navigation bar) match the page background
* An `Export data` link in [[ControlPanel|$:/ControlPanel]]
* An entrance to a JSON tiddler where custom action buttons on the toolbar can be configured
